# Workflow Rules

## Cycle
- `one` sends to `two`.
- `two` sends to `three`.
- `three` sends to `four`.
- `four` sends to `five`.
- `five` sends to `six`.
- `six` sends to `one`.
- `one` is the only agent that starts by sending without first receiving a handoff.
- `two`, `three`, `four`, `five`, and `six` must wait to receive a task from `ready_for_next_task.sh` before sending their handoff to the next agent.
- After `one` receives the handoff from `six`, `one` inspects handoff audit files and reports whether every expected handoff was sent and completed.
- After reporting status, `one` stops without sending another handoff.

## Final Status Check
- The final status check belongs only to `one`.
- Inspect the handoff `sent` and `inbox/completed` audit files for `one`, `two`, `three`, `four`, `five`, and `six`.
- Confirm these sent handoffs: `one` to `two`, `two` to `three`, `three` to `four`, `four` to `five`, `five` to `six`, and `six` to `one`.
- Confirm these completed handoffs: `two` from `one`, `three` from `two`, `four` from `three`, `five` from `four`, `six` from `five`, and `one` from `six`.
- Report `PASS` only if every expected sent and completed handoff is present. Otherwise report `FAIL` and list the missing or inconsistent entries.
